Incubation of nGOs with human vascular smooth muscles cells (hVSMCs) does not show any sign of cytotoxicity on cells. Moreover, the cell grows and morphology was found to be normal. The phase-contrast microscope images showed a gradual increase in cell counts without significant change in morphology, which indicates the cytocompatibility nature of nGOs (Fig. 12
                        ). At the end of each time points, cells were quantified using the MTS assay and results revealed that there was no significant reduction on cell growth and the cells proliferate was at a normal rate. This confirmed the compatible and safe behaviour of prepared nGOs for bioimaging applications (Fig. 13
                        ). The reason for the non-toxic nature of nGOs might be due to its hydrophilic surface and high dispersibility owing to the presence of more oxygenous functional groups (COOH and OH) on its surface [81–83]. Therefore, even in the presence of functional groups nGOs on the surface, the delocalized π electrons of basal plane of GO exert adsorptive capabilities of drugs, active substances and biomolecules via covalent bonding that leads to application in-vitro cell imaging [81,82].
